						<sci:help>The user who registered this component.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>scitegic/hub</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="RegistrationDate" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The date this component was registered.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>Tue Mar 23 16:26:51 2021</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentLocalID" type="LongType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>Local Component Identifier</sci:help>
						<sci:value>12</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="SubProtocolMadeLinkIntoCopy" type="BoolType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>Subprotocol Made Link Into Copy</sci:help>
						<sci:value>0</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="SubProtocolModified" type="BoolType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>Subprotocol Modified</sci:help>
						<sci:value>0</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Component Path" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The original path within the database of this component.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>Components\Database and Application Integration\Utilities\Prototypes\Application Integration\Foundation Hub\Utilities\Hub Connector</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
				</sci:component>
				<sci:protocol/>
			</sci:data>
			<sci:data object="SciTegic.VJSONReader.1">
				<sci:component name="Data from JSON" version="2">
					<sci:arg name="JSON Property" type="PropertyNameType" required="true" visibility="visible" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The property name of the property that will contain the JSON, as a string.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>response</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Join Behavior" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="visible" multi="false" uimpl="false">
						<sci:help>&lt;p&gt;How to merge the created data record onto the incoming data record. Options are:&lt;/p&gt;
 
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;OverwriteOrCreate&lt;/i&gt;: Copies all properties from the joining data onto the base data, overwriting the values of any properties that already exist.
&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;OverwriteExisting&lt;/i&gt;: Copies only those properties from the joining data to the base data that already exist on the base.
&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;CreateIfNew&lt;/i&gt;: Copies only those properties from the joining data to the base data that do not already exist on the base data.
&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;AppendOrCreate&lt;/i&gt;: The value of a joining property that already exists in the base data is appended  (as an array) to the value in the base property.  The other joining properties that are not already present in the base data are copied there.
&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;AppendExisting&lt;/i&gt;: The value of a joining property that already exists in the base data is appended  (as an array) to the value in the base property.  No other properties are copied. 
&lt;li&gt;&lt;i&gt;Replace&lt;/i&gt;: The input data record is replaced by the created data record. &lt;/ul&gt;

</sci:help>
						<sci:legalval>OverwriteOrCreate</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>OverwriteExisting</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>CreateIfNew</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval selected="true">AppendOrCreate</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>AppendExisting</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Replace</sci:legalval>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Additional Options" type="GroupType" required="false" visibility="visible" multi="false" legalvalsenforced="false">
						<sci:help>Contains less commonly used parameters

</sci:help>
						<sci:member>Repeat Tag</sci:member>
						<sci:member>Repeat Level</sci:member>
						<sci:member>Format Options</sci:member>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Repeat Tag" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="visible" multi="false">
						<sci:help>If not provided, then all top-level objects in the Source are returned.

If provided, then each top-level object is scanned for nodes that have the given name, and only those nodes are returned. </sci:help>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Repeat Level" type="LongType" required="false" visibility="visible" multi="false" expanded="true">
						<sci:help>If not provided, or if provided and equal to 1, then all top-level objects in the Source are returned.

If provided and &gt;1, then each top-level object is scanned and the descendents on the requested level are returned.
</sci:help>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Format Options" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="visible" multi="true" expanded="true">
						<sci:metaproplist>
							<sci:propval name="SCI_MimeType">ACCL/TEXT</sci:propval>
						</sci:metaproplist>
						<sci:help>These are options that control interpretation of the JSON as it is converted into a Pipeline Pilot data record.

Options are:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Object Values Are Hash Tables:&lt;/b&gt; If selected, then object values that are objects themselves are parsed as hash table values. If not selected, then object values that are objects are added to the parent node as children.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Allow Duplicate Object Names:&lt;/b&gt; If selected, then duplicate object names are allowed. If not selected, then duplicate object names are detected and throw an error.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Mixed Arrays Use Value Arrays:&lt;/b&gt; If selected, then arrays containing mixed types are returned as ValueArrays. If not selected, and if the array contains only strings, floating-point numbers, integers, and booleans, then the minimally-abstract array type is used. (For example, an array of floating-point numbers and integers would be a DoubleArrayValue.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Convert Arrays-of-Arrays:&lt;/b&gt; If selected, then ValueArrays containing ValueArrays are converted into NDimensionalArrayValues if possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</sci:help>
						<sci:legalval>Object Values Are Hash Tables</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Allow Duplicate Object Names</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Mixed Arrays Use Value Arrays</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Convert Arrays-of-Arrays</sci:legalval>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentAttributes" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="hidden" multi="true">
						<sci:help>Component Attributes</sci:help>
						<sci:value>ComponentReturnsPass</sci:value>
						<sci:legalval selected="true">ComponentTakesInput</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>ComponentReturnsPass</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>ComponentReturnsFail</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>ComponentRunsLocal</sci:legalval>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="OnDataTypeError" type="StringType" required="true" visibility="hidden" multi="false">
						<sci:legalval selected="true">Halt</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Fail</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Pass</sci:legalval>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="OnGeneralError" type="StringType" required="true" visibility="hidden" multi="false">
						<sci:legalval selected="true">Halt</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Fail</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Pass</sci:legalval>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="CustomErrorText" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false"/>
					<sci:arg name="Source" type="ExpressionType" required="true" visibility="nevershow" multi="false" expanded="true" legalvalsenforced="false">
						<sci:metaproplist>
							<sci:propval name="SCI_HiddenParameter" boolVal="true"/>
							<sci:propval name="SCI_GetValueFromOrigValue">property://$(JSON Property)</sci:propval>
							<sci:propval name="SCI_GetValueFromOrigType">URLType</sci:propval>
						</sci:metaproplist>
						<sci:help>&lt;p&gt;
The name or path name for the source data. The source can be a file, a network resource, a data record property, or a global property.
&lt;/p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use a file path name for files&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use a network URL for network resources&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &quot;global://property-name&quot; for global properties&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</sci:help>
						<sci:member>Maximum</sci:member>
						<sci:value>&quot;property://&quot; . parameter(&apos;JSON Property&apos;)</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Maximum" type="LongType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:metaproplist>
							<sci:propval name="SCI_HiddenParameter" boolVal="true"/>
						</sci:metaproplist>
						<sci:help>The maximum number of data records to read (all if value is empty)</sci:help>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Object Values Are" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:metaproplist>
							<sci:propval name="SCI_HiddenParameter" boolVal="true"/>
						</sci:metaproplist>
						<sci:help>When a JSON value is of object type, this is how to interpret it -- as a child node of the current node, or as a hash table value on the current node.</sci:help>
						<sci:legalval selected="true">Child Nodes</sci:legalval>
						<sci:legalval>Hash Table Values</sci:legalval>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Registrant" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The user who registered this component.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>scitegic/generic</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="RegistrationDate" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The date this component was registered.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>Tue Sep 13 08:33:13 2016</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentDisplayName" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:value>Data from JSON</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentPoint" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:value>390 -455</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentIcon" type="StringType" required="true" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:value>DOCUMENTNODE</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentGUID" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:value>{C515C623-DA9A-414E-BD66-C14A922EFA60}</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="DerivedFrom" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The component this component is based upon.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>Plug In</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentDisabled" type="LongType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:value>0</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentHelp" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="true">
						<sci:value>100</sci:value>
						<sci:value>Augments the incoming data record with data from JSON text</sci:value>
						<sci:value>&lt;p&gt;
Reads a JSON-encoded string from the input data record property, global property, network resource, or file specified in the &lt;i&gt;Source&lt;/i&gt; parameter, and converts the JSON data into Pipeline Pilot data records.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The JSON string can represent a single object or a single array whose elements are objects. When the JSON data represents a single object, a single data record will be output. When the JSON data represents an array of objects, then one data record for each object in that array will be output.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The values of each name - value pair within an object can be scalar values (boolean, floating point, integer, or string) or arrays of scalar values. These name - value pairs will become properties of the new data records output by the component. The type of the value or array in Pipeline Pilot will be the most specific type that fits.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note:&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
To learn more about JSON, visit the &lt;a href=&quot;javascript:DoLink(&apos;http://www.json.org&apos;)&quot;&gt;JSON.org&lt;/a&gt; web site.
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
</sci:value>
						<sci:value>Generic</sci:value>
						<sci:value>Input data record containing a JSON source property (optional).</sci:value>
						<sci:value>Generic</sci:value>
						<sci:value>One or more new data records representing the objects in the JSON source.</sci:value>
						<sci:value>None</sci:value>
						<sci:value/>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Component Sticky Notes" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false"/>
					<sci:arg name="RegistrationVersion" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The server version when this component was registered</sci:help>
						<sci:value>17.1.0.119</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="ComponentLocalID" type="LongType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>Local Component Identifier</sci:help>
						<sci:value>13</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
					<sci:arg name="Component Path" type="StringType" required="false" visibility="nevershow" multi="false">
						<sci:help>The original path within the database of this component.</sci:help>
						<sci:value>Components\Data Access and Manipulation\Utilities\Converters\Data from JSON</sci:value>
					</sci:arg>
				</sci:component>
			</sci:data>
			<sci:data object="SciTegic.PropertyFunctions.1">
				<sci:component name="Remove Properties" version="2">
